The '''2014–15 season''' was '''[[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]''''s 112th season in their history, their 100th in the [[Football League]] and 102nd in the [[English football league system|league system of English football]]. It was their second season back in [[Football League One|League One]] after finishing 11th in the previous year.

==Pre-Season News==

After finishing 11th in the [[2013-14 Football League One]] campaign the Bantams kept the majority of the squad for this season. However captain [[Gary Jones (footballer born 1977)|Gary Jones]], winger [[Garry Thompson (footballer born 1980)|Garry Thompson]], midfielder [[Nathan Doyle]], defenders [[Matthew Bates]] and [[Nathan Curtis]] were all released along with youth players Jack Stockdill, Louie Swain and Jack Bentley.

Bradford signed midfielder [[Matthew Dolan (footballer)|Matthew Dolan]] on a 1 Year permanent deal after spending the 2013-14 season on loan from [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref name="bradfordcityfc1">{{cite web|title=Dolan Signed Up |url=http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/dolan-signed-up-1556259.aspx |work=Bradford City AFC |date=16 May 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140901223854/http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/dolan-signed-up-1556259.aspx |archivedate=1 September 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref> Also defender [[Rory McArdle]] signed a new 3 Year deal with the club. Midfielder [[Billy Knott]] signed for Bradford on a 2-year deal after being released from [[Sunderland A.F.C|Sunderland]], who is described as a 'high-intensity' and 'high-energy' styled player.<ref name="bradfordcityfc2">{{cite web |title=City Tie up Deal for Knott |url=http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/billy-knott-signs-1591204.aspx |work=Bradford City AFC |date=30 May 2014}}</ref> Bradford made their 3rd Summer signing ahead of the new campaign by signing midfielder [[Gary Liddle]], after he was released by [[Notts County F.C.|Notts County]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Liddle Enthused by City Move |url=http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/liddle-enthused-by-city-move-1627718.aspx |work=Bradford City AFC |date=9 June 2014}}</ref> Defender [[Stephen Darby]] signed a new 3-year deal with the club, who was also appointed as the club's new captain for the 2014-15 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=New Captain Darby Signs Fresh Deal |url=http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/darby-signs-new-deal-1627623.aspx |work=Bradford City AFC |date=9 June 2014}}</ref>

It was announced that [[Blackburn Rovers]] would visit the Bantams in a pre-season friendly. A day after this news was announced the annual match against [[Guiseley]] was revealed to be played on 15 July. Bradford will also travel to [[Northern Ireland]] for a pre-season tour as they did in the previous year. There they will face [[University College Dublin]] and [[Shelbourne F.C.]].

Another pre-season friendly match was confirmed on 29 May, it was announced the club would travel to [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]]'s [[Globe Arena (football stadium)|Globe Arena]] on 2 August. That will be the first of two matches played within just over a week between the two clubs after they were both drawn together for the first round of the [[Football League Cup]], which will be played in the week commencing 11 August again at the [[Globe Arena (football stadium)|Globe Arena]].

